<br>
But let me tell you, after taking about $2000 worth of FAKE checks that looked real and even passed through our machines, that you have every right to refuse a suspicious check.  <br>
<br>
I didn't think that many gas stations took checks.  I always thought it was a cash or credit only type thing for most.  At least, when I pass through places on a road trip, I always see signs stating 'We do not take out of town checks.'<br>
<br>
And for every person who tells me that they're going to boycott our store and tell their friends not to come, I like to tell them to go right ahead.  Honestly, their three friends aren't going to harm our business one bit.<br>
